            <div class="prose max-w-none" x-show="lang === 'en'" x-cloak>
                <h2>Three Key TikTok Shop Changes This Week</h2>
<p>The Yiyu Digital team observed several notable platform developments while assisting clients with their campaigns this week.</p>
<p><strong>Extended Content Review Cycles</strong></p>
<p>Starting this week, some accounts reported that ad creative review times extended from the previous 2-4 hours to 8-12 hours. Queue backlogs directly impacted campaign launch timelines, particularly affecting teams needing rapid testing ahead of seasonal promotions.</p>
<p><strong>Natural and Paid Traffic Coordination Adjustments</strong></p>
<p>The platform is testing new traffic distribution logic in certain categories (beauty, 3C accessories): if a paid ad's cold launch performance falls below baseline metrics, the system automatically reduces exposure weight while decreasing organic recommendations for the same creative. This makes the first 24 hours of any creative's performance more critical than ever.</p>
<p><strong>High-Similarity Creatives Subject to流量限制</strong></p>
<p>Previously, creative deduplication mainly targeted repeated submissions within the same account. This week, cross-account similar creatives were also included in流量restrictions. Yiyu Digital recommends e-commerce teams with multiple sub-accounts audit their creative libraries to avoid mutual cannibalization from identical videos across different accounts.</p>
<hr />
<h2>Real Pressure on New Product Cold Launches</h2>
<p>These changes, combined with existing market conditions, have increased both the cost and timeline for cold launches. A home goods client served by Yiyu Digital this week reported their new product's organic conversion rate dropped approximately 15% compared to the same period last month, while CPMs rose by 8-12%.</p>
<p>The core tension: the platform expects creatives to prove their value during cold launch, but new products inherently lack historical data and user recognition. Relying on one or two creatives for repeated testing carries increasingly high risk.</p>
<hr />
<h2>Four Actionable Recommendations for Building Creative Libraries</h2>
<p><strong>1. Build Your Pool Before Testing, Don't Run Naked</strong></p>
<p>Before launching, prepare 8-15 creatives with different styles, formats, and selling points. Suggested ratio: 3-4 product feature demonstrations, 2-3 scenario-based lifestyle content, 2-3 user testimonial/UGC style pieces, 2-3 price hooks/promotional messages. A diversified creative pool increases the probability of at least one creative passing cold launch successfully.</p>
<p><strong>2. Control Creative Similarity, Improve Deduplication Efficiency</strong></p>
<p>Even for different creatives of the same product, make clear distinctions in: opening hooks (first 3 seconds), subtitle positioning, background music, on-screen talent approach, and camera angles. Yiyu Digital's internal tools support creative similarity detection to identify high-similarity combinations in advance.</p>
<p><strong>3. Reserve Creative Warm-Up Windows</strong></p>
<p>Don't submit creatives only when campaigns need to launch. We recommend uploading 24-48 hours in advance to clear the basic review queue, avoiding review delays disrupting投放schedules. You can also run some creatives first on the storefront's organic traffic (short video with product links) to accumulate initial engagement data before switching to paid投放.</p>
<p><strong>4. Establish Creative Lifecycle Tracking</strong></p>
<p>During cold launch, record each creative's core metrics (CTR, CPC, add-to-cart rate) at 6-hour intervals. If a creative's CTR falls 30% or more below category average in the first 12 hours, consider pausing and replacing it to avoid spending budget on underperforming creatives.</p>
<hr />
<h2>Key Recommendations for This Week</h2>
<p>TikTok Shop's traffic mechanisms are transitioning from "loose entry, strict exit" to "strict entry, strict exit." The scale and quality of your creative library will directly determine cold launch success. We recommend that投放teams audit existing creative libraries this week, organize high-similarity creatives, and prepare a batch of differentiated content ahead of the upcoming peak season traffic competition.</p>
